# Dev-harness reverse-proxy targets. Copy to .env.local (gitignored) and set the
# backends you test against. The https dev harness can't fetch http backends
# directly (mixed-content block), so Vite proxies them server-side.
#
# When set, a relative route is registered and forwards to the target:
#   /navidrome/* -> $NAVIDROME_PROXY_TARGET/*
#   /jellyfin/*  -> $JELLYFIN_PROXY_TARGET/*
#
# Then point the provider's Base URL at the route (e.g. /navidrome) instead of
# the raw http URL, so its API calls and the <audio> stream src both go through
# the proxy. Leave a var unset to skip its route.

# NAVIDROME_PROXY_TARGET=http://navidrome.lan:4533
# JELLYFIN_PROXY_TARGET=http://jellyfin.lan:8096
